info: The Church of Saint Nichlaus, located in Stará Ľubovňa, is a Roman Catholic church dating from 1280. There are several works of art in its baroque interior, including a late 13th century triumphal arch, late–Gothic stone font, the figure of the “Ľubovňa Madonna” dated 1360, the Gothic sacrament-house, and the late–Gothic tombstones.
name: St Nicholas Church

info: Ski resort in the Selce
name: Lyžiarske stredisko Selce

info: Museum in Banská Bystrica
name: Zväz múzeí na Slovensku

info: The Central Slovak Gallery in Banská Bystrica is the third oldest regional gallery in Slovakia and of all regional galleries, it has the most differentiated creative concept - regional art and Slovak art, Slovak graphic art, foreign graphic art.
name: Central Slovakia Gallery - Praetorium

info: Radvanský Manor House, was a centre of Radvaň and the seat of family Radvanský. It was built at the beginning of the 16th century. In the second half of the 20th century there was a State District Archive in the manor house. Today it is not used and is waiting for a new owner. In Radvaň still stands the Barczy Manor House from 1651, built on Gothic foundations.
name: Manor house Radvansky

info: House of slovak novelist, playwright, poet, teacher, and politician.
name: House of Jozef Gregora Tajovsky

info: Ski resort near Banská Bystrica
name: Ski Králiky

info: The Francis Xavier Cathedral, Banská Bystrica is a cathedral at Slovak National Uprising Square in Banská Bystrica, Slovakia.
name: St Francis Xavier Cathedral

info: The parish church of St. Elizabeth in Zvolen is a national cultural monument.
name: Church of St. Elizabeth

info: Alongside ancient Catholic Cathedral of the St. Nicholas in Prešovstands a younger Evangelical Church of the Holy Trinity from mid-17th century, one of the few Evangelical churches in Slovakia built during the time of the Reformation.
name: Evangelical Church of the Holy Trinity

info: A ski park in beautiful Donovaly
name: PARK SNOW Donovaly

info: Pilgrimage place in Litmanová
name: Hora Zvir

info: Rafting through the river Poprad in Poland
name: Rafting Poprad marina Pure Frajda

name: Redemptorist monastery with church

info: Ski resort in Szczawnica, Poland
name: The Ski-Jaworki Homole

info: The idea of creating the Pieniny Museum appeared in the interwar period and was realized in the 1950s. It was created to commemorate the history of Szczawnica and the life of the Pieniny highlanders. In addition to unusual exhibitions, you can also find a variety of ethnographic collections and more.
name: Pieniny Museum

info: The present Palace was erected on an originaly Gothic parcel in 1805 by classical reconstruction of a Baroque palace. On the tympanum are embossed coats of arms of the Csaky and Dessewffy families.
name: Csáky - Dezőfi palace

info: At the corner of Mlynská and Štefánikova streets in Košice, there is a beautiful historic building built in the neo-Gothic style. It is the Jacob's Palace, also known as Dzivák's Palace. This architectural gem, which attracts the views of passers-by, was built between 1899 and 1903 by the designer Ing. Arpád of Jacob, after which the palace also bears its name.
name: Jakab palace

info: Botanical garden in Košice
name: Botanical Garden UPJŠ

info: The memorial, built in honour of its coat of arms, is situated in the southern part of the central square in Košice. The coat of arms of Košice was created as early as in 1369. Košice was the first town in Europe to be given the right to use its own coat of arms by the sovereign Louis I.
name: Coat of Arms

info: Birthplace of the designer of the Corinth Canal. Just a short distance from the exit from the underground museum you can witness the statue of Košice-born engineer Béla Gerster – designer of well-known ship-ways, canals and railways, including the Panama Canal or the Corinth Canal.
name: Gerster house

info: The unique archaeological complex of the city fortification from 13th century.
name: Lower Gate

info: A fountain right next to the gothic style church.
name: Fountain by Church Of St. Michael

info: A church bell dedicated to Saint Urban, the patron of vine-dressers. The bell was cast in a mould by the bell-founder Franciscus Illenfeld of Olomouc in 1557. Its weight is seven tonnes
name: Bell Urban

info: Large, tree-lined water feature with dancing jets, music & colorful nighttime illuminations.
name: The Singing Fountain

info: Bridges of love, on which people place locks as symbols of their love, are now in almost every world metropolis. We also have one in Košice. It is located next to Jacob's Palace. Even couples in love from Košice place locks on it and believe that their love will last. Do
name: Bridge of love
Trinity Column with a sculpture of the Holy Trinity

info: Park with a Fountain with Zodiac Signs
name: Fountain of signs

info: St Anna's Church, Žbince is a Roman Catholic church in Žbince, Slovakia
name: Church of Saint Anna

info: Hradová Lookout Tower is located on the top of the hill with the same name and offers a beautiful view of the city of Košice, Košice Basin, Hornád Valley and the surrounding mountains. Thanks to the proximity to the city center, it is easily accessible.
name: Hradová Lookout Tower

info: The fountain was unveiled at Hviezdoslav Square in the second half. XIX century. The author of the neo-Baroque design was the famous local sculptor - Viktor Tilgner. The fountain adorns the main entrance of the monumental building of the Slovak National Theater.
name: Ganymede's Fountain

info: The House of the Good Shepherd (Slovak: Dom U dobrého pastiera) is a narrow, Rococo-style building in Bratislava, Slovakia, located in the Old Town below Bratislava Castle.
name: House of the Good Shepherd

info: The Slovak National Theater (Slovak: Slovenské národné divadlo, abbr. SND) is the oldest professional theatre in Slovakia, consisting of three ensembles: opera, ballet, and drama.
name: Slovak National Theatre

info: Janko Kráľ Park is a park in Bratislava's Petržalka borough.
name: Janko Kráľ Park

info: This neo-classical palace, formerly owned by Count Franz Zichy.
name: Zichy Palace

info: Chatam Sofer Memorial, formerly the Old Jewish Cemetery is the burial place and memorial of Moses Sofer, a prominent orthodox rabbi from the 19th century, built on the site of a 17th-century Jewish cemetery in Bratislava, Slovakia.
name: Chatam Sofer

info: The Slovak National Museum is the largest cultural institution in Slovakia. Museum preserves more than 3.8 million collection items. It is the most important institution focusing on scientific research and cultural education in the field of museology in Slovakia.
name: Slovak National Museum

info: This museum presents the life and work of the Bratislava-born sculptor A. Fleischmann (1896 – 1990), who worked in six countries on four continents. The museum presents his ceramic works from the period of the 1930s, as well as a selection of later works – mainly works from plexiglass, in the use of which he became a pioneer.
name: Arthur Fleischman

info: Zoya Gallery and Zoya Museum are two independent private institutions that focus on private art collection and art exhibition activities, in particular, on Slovak artists of the 20th and 21st centuries.
name: Zoya Gallery

info: The Grassalkovich Palace is a palace in Bratislava and the residence of the president of Slovakia. It is situated on Hodžovo námestie, near the Summer Archbishop's Palace. The building is a Rococo-late Baroque summer palace with a French garden.
name: Presidential Palace

info: The planet of peace is a fountain located in front of the Presidential Palace in Bratislava. There is a globe over 21 meters high on the water. It is decorated with images of pigeons - symbols of peace.
name: Planet of Peace Fountain

info: A casino in Bratislava
name: Banco Casino

info: Restored market hall & cultural-events venue built in 1910, holding farmers' & street-food markets.
name: Stara Trznica

info: The Trenčín Synagogue is a building in the city of Trenčín in Slovakia
name: Trenčín Synagogue

info: The oldest pilgrim site in Slovakia - Skalka is located on the way from Trenčín to Nemšová. It consists of two objects: Malá Skalka and Veľká Skalka.
name: Pilgrimage place Skalka at Trencin

info: A park located in Trencin
name: Park Jána Baltazára Magina

info: A museum located in the Beckov Castle
name: Beckov museum

info: Ski resort in Vápenice, Czechia
name: Ski centre Bílé Karpaty

info: Beckov Castle is a castle in ruins located near the village of Beckov in Nové Mesto nad Váhom District, Trenčín Region, western Slovakia. It is a natural cultural monument and its present appearance is the result of renovations in the last quarter of the twentieth century and since 2002.
name: Castle of Beckov

info: In the headquarters of the Trenčín Museum, in the building of Zupa House, there is a permanent exhibition : From the history and culture of the free royal town of Trenčín and the former Trenčín zupa (county)
name: Trenčín Museum in Trencin

info: The gallery, constituted 40 years ago, was named after M. A. Bazovský, one of the founders of modern Slovak painting who spent the last years of his dramatic life in this town. The gallery found its home in the architecturally attractive baroque Piarist monastery.
name: Galéria Miloša Alexandra Bazovského

info: The Castle is the most important dominant of the town Levice. It is from the end of the 13th century. It stands on top of volcanic rock protuberance above the swamps of the Hron river. It was the sentry fort guarding the road leading to central Slovakian mining towns.
name: Levice castle

info: Brekov Castle is a ruined Gothic and Renaissance era stone castle above the village of Brekov in Humenné District, Prešov Region, in east Slovakia. It is a hilltop castle located on a cone-shaped hill with a limestone bedrock, in an altitude of approximately 480 m above sea level.
name: Brekov Castle

info: The Viniansky Castle ruin is located by the village of Vinné. The Gothic castle was probably built in the second half of the 13th century as a guard castle to protect the trade route leading to Poland. Already in 1312, the castle was attacked and damaged by Omodej noble family.
name: Viniansky Castle

info: The Castle is known for its “Book of Lies and Liars” held here in the 16th and 17th centuries, also referred to as the Book of Čičava - in which curious lies and names of liars were noted. The Slovak idiom “it should be entered in the Čičava Book” is still used and it refers to outrageous or bold lies.
name: Castle Čičva

info: Vihorlat Protected Landscape Area is one of 14 protected landscape areas in Slovakia. The Landscape Area is in the middle part of the Vihorlatské vrchy mountains, in eastern Slovakia. It is in the Humenné, Sobrance and Snina districts.
name: Vihorlat Protected Landscape Area

info: Almost in the center of Humenné, on a rather rugged terrain, there is an open-air museum with an exposition of folk architecture and housing. The open-air museum in Humenné is relatively small but rich in folk architecture.
name: Open-air museum Humenné

info: The town of Humenné, one of the historical centres of the Zemplín region, is adorned by a Renaissance manor house of imposing size. The residence guarded by two bronze lions was commissioned to be built by the wealthy and powerful Drugeth family.
name: Manor house Humenne

info: The Humenský Sokol nature trail is located only two kilometers south of the town of Humenné. It passes through the National Nature Reserve of the same name. The route is 3.5 kilometers long. Here you will find a representation of grass and forest plant communities. There is also Jaskyňa Dúpna cave, where six species of bats hibernate during the winter season.
name: Humenský Sokol Nature Trail

info: Jasenov Castle is a ruined Gothic and Renaissance era stone castle above the village of Jasenov in Humenné District, Prešov Region, in east Slovakia. It is a hilltop castle located on a fairly steep, roughly cone-shaped hill with a limestone bedrock, in an altitude of approximately 392 m above sea level.
name: Castle Jasenov

info: Stropkov manor house is the last preserved part of the town castle, which was built in the 15th century by the then owners of the town Perényi family in the Gothic-Renaissance style.
name: Manor house Stropkov

info: The Andy Warhol Museum of Modern Art in Medzilaborce, Slovakia, was established in 1991 by the American family of the artist Andy Warhol and the Slovak Ministry of Culture. Until 1996, AWMMA was called The Warhol Family Museum of Modern Art.
name: Andy Warhol Museum of Modern Art

info: Cemetary of the fallen in Wold War 1
name: World War 1 cemetary

info: The prince Laborec was patron of the whole cross- country valley. Statue of prince is over 5 meters high and it stands on nearly two meters natural stone stand. In the pedestal under the staute is box with soil of Ruthenian villages that represents unity of Ruthenians.
name: Prince Laborec's statue

info: East Carpathians Protected Landscape Area is a protected landscape area in north-eastern Slovakia, in the Prešov Region, in the Carpathian Mountains. The PLA occupies a slice of land along with the border with Poland.
name: East Carpathians Protected Landscape Area

info: Beaver lodge in nature reservatiion Velky Les
name: Beaver lodge Veľký Les

info: A charming waterfall in Poland
name: Wodospad w Dołżycy

info: Museum near the city Presov
name: City Museum and Gallery Velky Saris

info: Restored 19th-century synagogue with Moorish design touches, ornate decor & a small history museum.
name: Jewish Orthodox Synagogue

info: The manor house in Fintice has an irregular floor plan. It is believed that it was based on a mansion built by the first owners of the manor house. The manor house’s tower was built in the 16th century by the Darhol family who owned the municipality of Fintice.
name: Fintice Manor-House

info: Šariš Castle is a ruined Gothic and Renaissance era stone castle above the town of Veľký Šariš in Prešov District, Prešov Region, Slovakia. It is a hilltop castle located on a cone-shaped hill with a wide plateau at its top, in an altitude of approximately 570 m above sea level.
name: Saris castle

info: The Co-Cathedral of Saint Nicholas in Prešov is one of the oldest and most important churches in Slovakia. External dimensions of concathedral are 54.7 meters in length, 34.45 in width. The height of indoor nave is 16 m and tower reaches a height of 71 meters.
name: Co-Cathedral of Saint Nicholas

info: The Regional Museum in Prešov was originally established as the Municipal Museum in 1945. Currently located at the historical Rákoczi’s Palace in the town centre. Currently, the museum houses exhibitions of regional character.
name: Regional Museum in Prešov

info: The Neptune Fountain stands at the Market Square in Prešov. The statue of the sea lord was made in the first half of the 19th century by Košice mason Vincent Staviarsky. It depicts Neptune leaning on a trident. Around him you can see the forms of aquatic animals.
name: Neptune Fountain

info: A sculpture laid on the sidewalk iron plate in a direction parallel with the passage of description. Residents and visitors to the city can be proud of that monument 49 passing parallel they move from one geographical parallels to another.
name: Monument 49 Latitude Presov

info: A peak part of West Tatras
name: Dlhý úplaz

info: Fitting almost 6.000 visitors, the magnificent church in Sv. Kriz is one of the largest wooden constructions in Central Europe. Its ground plan has a shape of a cross and is 43m long.
name: Wooden Articular Church of Svaty Kriz

info: In 1886 the forest botanical park was established at the other place – near by the newly built school area. On 1st December, 1982 the arboretum was declared a protected study area.
name: Liptovský Hrádok arboretum

info: Authentic premises of the Old Protestant Vicarage reflect the atmosphere of the first half of the 19th century when Tatrín was established and Requirements of Slovak Nation were elaborated. Exposition has furniture typical for that period; there are facsimiles of historical documents, records, photographs and original portraits of personalities by Janko Alexy.
name: Exposition Tatrín and Requirements of Slovak Nation

info: Catholic church in Liptovský Mikuláš
name: Church of St. Peter from Alkantara

info: Modrn Laser Tag arena in Liptovsky Mikuláš
name: LIPTOVLASERS - LASER ARÉNA

info: The house, which was originally built as an expression of frustration over red tape, soon turned into a popular tourist attraction. The building is located near the town of Liptovský Mikuláš close to the aqua park.
name: Heliport Liptov

info: A park with world famous buildings models. There is a train, an autodrome and jumping castle for kids. There is also a restaurant.
name: Tatrapolis- World of Fantasy

info: At the end of the village Liptovský Ján, there is a place that shows healing effects. It is a thermal spring called Kaďa. The natural spa spring is surrounded by the beauty of the Jánska Valley and together they create an ideal place for recreation and relaxation.
name: Thermal springs Kaďa

info: Slovakia is known to be a culturally rich country. There are many historical monuments in our territory and many of them are unique in Europe. For this reason, the MINI SLOVAKIA park was created, whose creators want to revive public interest in this wealth.
name: Park Mini Slovakia

info: Rosenfeld Palace located in the historic center of Žilina has a rich history. It was built in 1907 as a miniature imitation of Vienna's Belvedere Castle. The palace is one of the most beautiful monuments in the city and the largest cultural monument in the property, which has been preserved almost in its original condition.
name: Rosenfeld Palace

info: Entertainment centre for children in Zilina
name: CONGO - Entertainment Center

info: The manor-house in Radola is one of the oldest historical monuments in Kysuce, Slovakia. Historical research suggests that the oldest part of the building dates to between 1550 and 1575.
name: The Manor-house in Radola

info: The Budatín Castle is a castle in north-western Slovakia, near the city of Žilina, where the Kysuca river flows into the Váh river.
name: Budatin Castle

info: The Museum of Považie in Žilina is situated in the premises of the Budatín Castle on the northern outskirts of Žilina.
name: Museum of Povazie region

info: A Baroque statue standing in the middle of Mariánske Square comes from 1738. Jozef Matulaj, the Žilina senator donated to the town the money for the wages of a priest, chaplain, professors, spital and for construction and maintenance of the Immaculata statue.
name: Immaculata

info: The tower stands on Horný Val street, next to the parish church. Its history is linked to the name of Strečno castle’s owner from 1526 to 1529, Burian Svetlovský of Vlčnov.
name: Burian’s tower

info: Church of the Conversion of Saint Paul in Žilina is a church in Slovakia. Church of the Conversion of Saint Paul in Žilina is situated nearby to La Donuteria, and close to Kláštor kapucínov.
name: Conversion of St Paul Church

info: The Museum of Art in Žilina was established in 1976 when it became independent from The Museum of Považie. Its exhibition activities at the end of the 70s and in the 80s were focused mainly on contemporary Slovak drawing, which the Museum of Art regularly showcased.
name: Museum of Art in Žilina

info: The renaissance parish stairway was built in 1568 as a defence passageway serving the members of the city art’s guilds to defend city walls ranging from the St. Michael’s Carner to Trenčín Castle. The stairway also served as an access road to the town armory.
name: Fontána Srdce

info: Cathedral of the Assumption is a Roman Catholic cathedral in Rožňava, Slovakia. It is the seat of Bishop of Rožňava.
name: Assumption of Mary Church

info: The Krásna Hôrka Castle is a castle in Slovakia, built on a hilltop overlooking the village of Krásnohorské Podhradie near Rožňava, in Košice Region. The first recorded mention of the castle was in 1333. In 1961 Krásna Hôrka was designated a National Cultural Monument of the Slovak Republic.
name: Krasna Horka Castle

info: This hunting estate of almost 50 rooms was owned by the noble Bebek family and then Andrássy family for centuries. The town of Roznava has been very blessed. It lies in the shadow of two distinctive historical sites: Krasna Horka Castle and the manor house in Betliar.
name: Manor House of Betliar

info: Wasserburg is a smaller water castle in Štítnik, Slovakia
name: Wasserburg Šťítnik

info: The Sentinel Adventure Center was created by the reconstruction of the buildings of Mining Museum in Rožňava. Its premises include Exposition of mining and metallurgy of Gemer, exposition of times of steam in the Mining Museum, mining workshops and exposition of nature of the Slovak Karst.
name: Sentinel - Mining Experience Center

info: Aggtelek National Park is a national park in Northern Hungary, in the Aggtelek Karst region. The most significant values of the national park are the special surface formations and caves in this limestone landscape.
name: Aggtelek National Park

info: The Slovak Karst (Slovak: Slovenský kras) is one of the mountain ranges of the Slovenské Rudohorie Mountains in the Carpathians in southern Slovakia. A lot of caves are availible to visit in there.
name: Slovak Karst

info: Ochtinská Aragonite Cave represents a unique natural phenomenon drawing attention by the richness and variety of aragonite fill, as well as an interesting evolution and development of cave spaces.
name: Ochtinská Aragonite Cave
Gombasek Cave
category: Gombasecká Cave belongs among the most important caves of the Slovak Karst national park. It is known mostly by occurrence of thin straw stalactites. Within the „Caves of Slovak and Aggtelek Karst“ it was inscribed on the world heritage list.

info: The Mining Museum in Rožňava, which is more than a hundred years old, is one of three specialized mining museums in Slovakia and serves as the district museum of national history and geography. Its function is to preserve not only artifacts from the field of mining and metallurgy, but also collections from various disciplines.
name: Mining Museum in Rožňava

info: Rock near Roznava with an amazing view.
name: Monkey rock

info: The early Baroque single-nave Church of St. Joseph, is an example of a Protestant tower-less hall church. This construction characteristic reflects the many eventful decades of the fight for religious freedom.
name: Church of St. Joseph

info: The first Early Baroque building of national significance in Slovakia, the  university Cathedral of St John the Baptist is one of the most valuable historical monuments of Trnava.
name: Cathedral of St. John the Baptist

info: One of the entrance gates through the walls to old Trnava. Nicely renovated. Now additionally enriched with period characters that are part of the game.
name: Bernolákova gate

info: It stands on the Slanický ostrov island. A memorial was built there to commemorate its famous native. In 1953 five villages of the Orava region disappeard under the water level of the Oravská priehrada dam. Among them was the village of Slanica where in 1762 Anton Bernolák was born.
name: Memorial of Anton Bernolák

info: The City Tower (in Slovak Mestská veža) is one of the most important historic monuments of Trnava, Slovakia. The tower's construction began on 28 July 1574. In 1666 and 1683 the tower was affected by fire and since then it has remained without a roof.
name: City Tower
